# Component Patterns

## Before Creating New Components

**Search existing components first.** Reuse or extend:

- **Atoms:** `VideoPlayer`, `LargeVideoPlayer`, `PlayListCard`, `PlayListItemCard`, `ColorSchemeToggle`, `CountUp`, `Welcome`
- **Molecules:** `Navigation`, `Footer`, `HpAbout`, `Pagination`
- **Organisms:** `Splash`

## Atomic Design

- **atoms/** — Smallest units (buttons, cards, single-purpose UI)
- **molecules/** — Composed atoms (Footer, Navigation, Pagination)
- **organisms/** — Complex sections (Splash, page-level compositions)

## Component Folder Structure

Each component lives in its own folder:

```
ComponentName/
  index.ts          # re-exports default + named exports
  ComponentName.tsx
  ComponentName.module.css
```

## Mantine Usage

- Use `@mantine/core` components: `Card`, `Button`, `Text`, `Title`, `Group`, `Stack`, `Flex`, `Container`, etc.
- Use `@mantine/hooks`: `useResizeObserver`, `useMediaQuery`, `useDisclosure`, `useElementSize`, `usePagination`
- Use `@tabler/icons-react` for icons
- Theme color `ytRed` for primary actions
- Use `decode` from `html-entities` for user-generated text (e.g. YouTube titles)

## Patterns

- Use a `displayText` object for all user-facing strings (accessibility, consistency)
- Use `gaEvent` from `~/utils/gtags.client` for analytics on external links/buttons
- Import and use utils from `~/utils/utils` (e.g. `sixteenByNine`, `createSrcSet`, `truncate`, `findIndex`)
